race.description: Harris Accident Repair Centre Maiden Plate
race.comment: JUMPINMYCAR (3) stepped out at Pakenham on debut (heavy track) and finished the race off okay after being slow into stride. He'd been well educated and can sit closer today. Drops back to country grade and will be tough to beat. WACO KID (6) resumed in the same race, better supported, but also settled back and was never in the hunt. He brought strong soft track provincial form to that and is likely to improve quickly. SHOT OF SATIN (12) peaks off close-up placings at Ballarat and Seymour. She races forward and will get every chance to break through. LAWN BOWLER (4) is a leader who should go a lot better dropping back to a shorter sprint. Jumps from the inside barrier, and he will find this grade easier.
